quantitative_claims:
Phage vB_AbaM-SHI formed the plaques with around 5 mm in diameter ( 
 Figure 1A 
 ).

TEM images showed that phage vB_AbaM-SHI virions have a tail with a length of around 30 nm and an icosahedral head with an estimated diameter of 60 nm ( 
 Figure 1C 
 ).

We used ImageJ to measure capsule width in 100 cells per strain with 3 measurements taken per cell, which revealed average capsule widths of 0.142 µM ± 0.010, 0.072 µM ± 0.008, and 0.092 µM ± 0.008 in VIR-O, AV-T, and AV-T Δ 1132 , respectively ( 
 Figure 3E 
 ).
